'''Condurrite''' is a name given to a mixture of [[cuprite]], [[domeykite]] and [[tenorite]]. It takes its name from the Great Condurrow Mine at [[Troon, Cornwall|Troon]], [[Cornwall]] in the United Kingdom, which is regarded as the [[Type locality (geology)|type locality]].<ref>[http://www.mindat.org/min-10070.html Condurrite: Condurrite mineral information and data<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

