{{About|the scientific journal||Landslide (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox journal | cover = Landslides (academic journal).jpg | editor = K. Sassa | discipline = [[Earth sciences]], [[engineering]] | abbreviation = Landslides | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media]] | country = | frequency = Monthly | history = 2004-present | openaccess = [[Hybrid open access journal|Hybrid]] | license = | impact = 3.811 | impact-year = 2017 | website = https://www.springer.com/earth+sciences+and+geography/natural+hazards/journal/10346 | link2 = https://link.springer.com/journal/volumesAndIssues/10346 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 456171837 | LCCN = 2007204176 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1612-510X | eISSN = 1612-5118 }} '''''Landslides''''' is a monthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering research on all aspects of [[landslide]]s. The topics covered by the journal range from landslide identification and monitoring, [[Remote sensing (geology)|remote sensing]], laboratory and field testing, to [[risk assessment]] and mitigation. It was established in 2004 as the official journal of the [[International Consortium on Landslides]] and is published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Kyoji Sassa ([[Kyoto University]]).<ref>{{cite web |title=Landslides - Editorial Board |url=https://www.springer.com/earth+sciences+and+geography/natural+hazards/journal/10346/PSE?detailsPage=editorialBoard |accessdate=2018-05-29 |publisher=Springer Science+Business Media}}</ref>
